{
  "stem": "11272.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The three older brothers, Phillip, Ben, and Bernie, were taken away to Hungarian labor camps, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Father, mother, my brother Bill, Sam, and I and my sister were there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In addition, there were my cousin and my uncles and aunts from the same village, Uncle Yosef, his wife, and their children.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And sadly, only one is alive today, and she's in Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was trapped in Russia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] then we were joined by a lot of other cousins and other family, but most of all, all my friends, basically the whole village.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Jewish people were there, and also the surrounding villages.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then they started bringing from the other side of the city-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Jews into-- into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, but-- but we weren't there that long, because the next thing we knew, they brought in cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was about three weeks, third week, something like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Time runs away from you when-- when-- when you're faced with such grief, and so you don't know days, you don't know nights a lot of times.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And next thing we knew, in the morning they pulled in cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they ordered us to leave everything and get into the cattle car.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, you know, at first we didn't want to leave everything, just like we didn't want to leave everything in our home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And there was no room in the cattle car, really.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they jammed in somewhere between 80 and 100 people in the cattle car.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a small car.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
